    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Psalms",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 4,
        "summary": "David pleads for mercy\u2014He counsels, Put your trust in the Lord.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Hear me when I call, O God of my righteousness: thou hast enlarged me when I was in distress; have mercy upon me, and hear my prayer.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 34:4; Micah 7:7; 1\u00a0Jn. 5:14 (13\u201314); Mosiah 9:18; Ether 1:40 (39\u201340).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 97:6 (5\u20136); Rom. 1:17; 2\u00a0Ne. 4:35; Ether 9:22; D&C 1:16.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 35:3; Ps. 118:5 (4\u20136); Isa. 25:4 (1, 4).",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "O ye sons of men, how long will ye turn my glory into shame? how long will ye love vanity, and seek after leasing? Selah.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Shame.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Vanity.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But know that the Lord hath set apart him that is godly for himself: the Lord will hear when I call unto him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Setting Apart.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Godliness.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Stand in awe, and sin not: commune with your own heart upon your bed, and be still. Selah.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Offer the sacrifices of righteousness, and put your trust in the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "There be many that say, Who will shew us any good? Lord, lift thou up the light of thy countenance upon us.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 67:1; 119:135; Alma 5:14; 3\u00a0Ne. 19:25 (24\u201325).",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 98
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou hast put gladness in my heart, more than in the time that their corn and their wine increased.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0grain.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I will both lay me down in peace, and sleep: for thou, Lord, only makest me dwell in safety.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contentment.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
